Reasoning: The paper deals with game theory models and algorithms for finding stable solutions in multiple partners matching games. This falls under the category of computational game theory, which is typically classified under cs.GT. The paper also discusses the core of the corresponding cooperative game, which is a topic in algorithmic mechanism design (cs.AI). The algorithmic aspects of the paper involve polynomial-time algorithms, which suggests that it may also be relevant to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses characterizations and proofs, which suggests that it may be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and mathematical aspects of computer science (cs.MA).
